



Gentn
Mount Vernon May 25th 1772



On the 27th Ulto I drew two Setts of Excha: on you in favour of Burwell Bassett Esqr.the one Sett for Two hundd pounds Sterg and the other for 133.6.8 to answer in part, the purchase of Land mentioned to you in a Letter of the 16th of March which sevl Sums you will please to pay & place to Acct of Mr Custis.1 I am Gentn Yr Most Obedt

Go: Washington

